The paper deals with graph algorithms and optimization techniques for map-reduce, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Databases (cs.DB), Data Mining (cs.DM), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). However, since the focus is on graph enumeration and query evaluation, cs.DS and cs.DB are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DM, cs.CC, and cs.AI.
